text:
BETTY GILPIN: It was a
Gloria Steinem mountaintop
of glitter and body slams.
[music playing]

- Ladies and gentlemen,
introducing the gorgeous ladies
of wrestling!
[cheering]

ALISON BRIE: I feel
like the best way

to decide my wrestler name
is, like, the same way

people decide their porn
name by using their,

like, first pet and the
first street they lived on.

So mine would be Sally
Montecito, which, like,
I don't know what it means.

But it just sounds cool,
like I'd just see Sally
Montecito entering the ring.

BETTY GILPIN: It would be
sort of a mix between Elaine
Stritch and Shirley Temple--

a cutesy song but,
like, a dark past.

KATE NASH: I'd have a
couple different dogs
on the-- on the go.

And I come into the
ring with, (SINGING)
"now I want to be your dog."

BRITNEY YOUNG: The Parallel
Parker and, like, just,

like, throw people
up against the ropes

and just, like, get
in there real tight.

JACKIE TOHN: Maybe
I'd be a squirrel
with, like, a huge, plush tail.

And just really wrestling
but that just tail

being annoying and in
everyone's face is funny to me.

REBEKKA JOHNSON: My wrestling
character would be, like,
straight out of "Jersey Shore."

And, believe me, I'd
take my earrings off.
I'd have teased hair.
I'd have fake tan.

And my fake tan
would rub off on you.
[musical tone]
